# 🛠️ Git & GitHub: The Master Reference

> **Git:** Local version control tool.
> **GitHub:** Cloud-based storage and collaboration platform.

## 0. Installation & Setup

On Windows, use **winget** for a quick install:

```powershell
# Visit https://git-scm.com/ for the installer OR run:
winget install --id Git.Git -e --source winget

```

---

## 1. Quick Reference Table
+-------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------------+
| Action            | Command                   | Purpose                                   |
+-------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------------+       
| **Initialize**    | `git init`                | Start a new local repository.             |
| **Clone**         | `git clone <url>`         | Download a project from GitHub.           |
| **Status**        | `git status`              | See which files are modified or staged.   |
| **Stage**         | `git add .`               | Prepare all changes for saving.           |
| **Commit**        | `git commit -m "msg"`     | Save changes with a descriptive note.     |
| **Push**          | `git push origin main`    | Send local code to GitHub.                |
| **Pull**          | `git pull`                | Fetch and merge changes from GitHub to PC.|
| **Log**           | `git log --oneline`       | View a clean history of all commits.      |
+-------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------------+

